The paper deals with the analysis of Markov chains for approximate sampling of matchings in graphs, which is a topic in both theoretical computer science and discrete mathematics. The focus on the mixing time of these chains suggests that the paper is likely to be classified under cs.DS (data structures and algorithms) or cs.CC (computational complexity). The use of graph theory and combinatorics in the analysis suggests that cs.DM (discrete mathematics) and cs.GT (graph theory) are also possible categories. Finally, the use of spectral gaps in the experimental investigation suggests that cs.IT (information theory) may also be a relevant category.
